description: Hash strings into numbers and then mod them into buckets.
name: hash-mod
readme:
# hash-mod

  Hash strings into numbers and then mod them into buckets

## Install

    npm install hash-mod

## Example

```js
var mod = require('hash-mod')(100);

mod('string');
// 13
```

## API

### hashMod(buckets)

  Returns a mod-hashing function that first takes the integer hash, and then mods it by `buckets`. Defaults to `100` buckets.
